What you need to know:  Of the local pros, Mohit Mediratta will be off first at 7.20am, followed by Zimbabwe’s Robson Chinhoi, while Justus Madoya will also tee off from 7.20am, but on the 10th tee, while Greg Snow and Dismas Indiza are in the afternoon draw.The course, which has been well prepared for this year’s Open, is in great condition and ready for the main event on Thursday where a field of 144 will be battling it out, with six of them being local amateurs led by Kenya’s leading amateur Adel Balala.